description: Popular TikTok creator Terryon Thomas, known as Mr Prada to nearly 4 million followers, has been arrested.
title: Popular TikTok creator Mr Prada arrested

description: Judge releases filing with new details in Trump election interference case; Israel prepares for response to Iranian missile attack, officials say; Biden, Harris tour storm-ravaged regions in the Southeast; and more on tonight’s broadcast.
title: Nightly News Full Broadcast (October 2nd)

description: The Maui wildfire that killed more than 100 people last year and destroyed Lahaina, Hawaii, was caused by downed power lines, investigators found.
title: Deadly Maui wildfire was sparked by downed power lines, investigation finds

description: Republicans could pass both a health care overhaul that would replace Obamacare and extend Trump tax breaks in one bill if they win Congress and the White House.
title: GOP senator eyes health care overhaul and extending Trump tax cuts in one big 2025 bill

description: Reno, Nev., like many American communities, has seen home prices rise drastically, putting the dream of home ownership out of reach for many people. Some are even being forced to delay having children. NBC News' Shannon Pettypiece reports on how the Trump and Harris campaigns would deal with the crisis.
title: Skyrocketing home prices force many to drastically alter their life plans

description: Facing what could be months without a steady water supply, the only solution for Mission Hospital was to dig a well. The Asheville, North Carolina hospital was crippled after Helene.
title: At Asheville's Mission Hospital, workers describe the dire conditions after the storm

description: Scientists are preparing to welcome a new guest from outer space to Earth's orbit. Steve Patterson reports on the coming close encounter with a "mini-moon."
title: Good News: Close encounter with a second moon

description: President Biden and Vice President Harris toured parts of the storm zone ravaged by Hurricane Helene. With the election less than five weeks away, the campaigns face several challenges, including the devastation from Hurricane Helene and the escalating conflict in the Middle East. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports
title: Biden, Harris tour storm-ravaged regions in the Southeast

description: The group, organized by former Trump national security adviser Robert O'Brien and former National Security Council chief of staff Alex Gray, wrote in a letter that "securing peace" is "the legacy of Trump."
title: Former Trump national security aides endorse him amid turmoil overseas

description: Election officials in Durham County, N.C., are putting the finishing touches on their newly fortified office, joining many other election offices around the country where officials have received threats. NBC News' Hallie Jackson reports.
title: After threats, officials fortify election offices ahead of voting

description: Republicans are giddy over the prospect of appointing new justices to the Supreme Court in a second Donald Trump presidential term.
title: The GOP's SCOTUS dreams: From the Politics Desk

description: GOP senators anticipate that in a second term, Trump would have at least one Supreme Court vacancy to fill. Democrats hope that prospect motivates their voters this fall.
title: Republicans expect to confirm even more Supreme Court justices if Trump wins

description: In surveillance video that captured the courthouse slaying of a Kentucky judge, the sheriff charged in the death appears to shoot at the judge multiple times while the judge crawled on the floor, scrambling for cover.
title: Deadly shooting of Kentucky judge at courthouse was captured on video

description: House Democrats need to flip just four seats to take the chamber’s majority in November, and super PACs are going all out on the airwaves in battleground districts, blasting Republicans over abortion and reproductive rights in ads.
title: Democrats lean on doctors in battleground ads on abortion — even when they're not from the district

description: A former Los Angeles police detective who killed a romantic rival and concealed the murder for more than two decades will not be paroled, reversing an earlier decision that found she was suitable for release, a lawyer for the victim’s family said Wednesday.
title: Ex-LAPD detective who hid murder for decades won't be paroled, reversing earlier decision

description: The CIA has released instructions in Farsi, Mandarin and Korean to make it safer for tipsters and informants to communicate “securely” with the agency.
title: The CIA is asking informants for secret tips in the national languages of Iran, North Korea and China

description: After Hurricane Helene, residents of Swannanoa, a mountain town in North Carolina, return to flattened homes, impassable roads and raw emotions.
title: A North Carolina mountain town is wrecked by Hurricane Helene

description: Haze and a chlorine odor will likely descend upon Atlanta on Thursday, more fallout from a BioLab chemical fire that ignited in Conyers, Georgia.
title: Atlanta likely to be covered by haze and chlorine odor from chemical lab fire, officials warn

description: Former President Donald Trump was "fundamentally" acting as a private candidate not as president when he sought to overturn his 2020 election loss, special counsel Jack Smith aruged in a new filing.
title: Trump 'resorted to crimes' to stay in office after 2020 loss, Jack Smith team says

description: Bertha Mendoza, 56, had just celebrated her birthday a week before Hurricane Helene floodwaters swept her away in Erwin, Tennessee.
title: Death of Tennessee plastics plant employee leaves a close-knit family in grief

description: DETROIT — Ford Motor lost its lead in electric vehicle sales to crosstown rival General Motors during the third quarter, as the automaker’s EV growth slowed.
title: Ford's third-quarter sales up 0.7% as GM overtakes it in EVs

description: Liberty Media-owned Formula One and luxury giant LVMH are entering into a 10-year partnership, according to a joint press release from the companies Wednesday afternoon.
title: LVMH and Formula One announce 10-year partnership

description: Starlink, the satellite internet service from SpaceX, is poised to become a crucial lifeline in parts of southern Appalachia that were devastated by Hurricane Helene.
title: Elon Musk's Starlink brings internet — and politics — to storm-ravaged areas

description: What are high-risk pools for health insurance? JD Vance proposed high risk pools for people with pre-existing conditions during the vice presidential debate.
title: Vance's high-risk pool health insurance plan: Will it help or harm sick patients?

description: Costco continues to chip away at the gold mine that is the precious metals market.
title: Costco adds platinum bars to its precious metals lineup

description: DETROIT — Stellantis’ U.S. new vehicle sales continued a yearslong free fall during the third quarter, despite CEO Carlos Tavares’ attempts to correct what he has called “arrogant” mistakes.
title: Stellantis U.S. auto sales extend free fall in third quarter

description: OpenAI has closed its long-awaited funding round at a valuation of $157 billion, including the $6.6 billion the company raised from an extensive roster of investment firms and big tech companies.
title: OpenAI closes funding at $157 billion valuation, as Microsoft, Nvidia, SoftBank join round

description: HARRISBURG, Pa. — Democratic Sen. Bob Casey and Republican Dave McCormick have sought to strike a balance with the top of the ticket in Pennsylvania, a state that will play a key role in determining control of both the White House and the Senate.
title: In Pennsylvania, Bob Casey and Dave McCormick strike a balance with the top of the ticket

description: Atlanta rapper Rich Homie Quan died last month in Georgia from an accidental drug overdose, authorities said.
title: Rich Homie Quan died from accidental drug overdose involving fentanyl and codeine

description: The U.S. Department of Justice has launched a review and evaluation of the 1921 race massacre in Tulsa, Oklahoma, Assistant Attorney General Kristen Clarke said.
title: Justice Department launches first federal review of 1921 Tulsa race massacre

description: A California doctor is expected to plead guilty Wednesday in a deal with federal prosecutors over the fatal overdose of “Friends” star Matthew Perry last year.
title: Doctor charged in Matthew Perry's overdose death expected to plead guilty

description: The death toll has risen to at least 175 across the Southeast since Hurricane Helene made landfall in Florida as a Category 4 storm last week, and hundreds are still missing amid the historic flooding.
title: Here's how to help victims of Hurricane Helene

description: The Welcome Corps is a program helping to resettle LGBTQ refugees fleeing countries that are cracking down on gay and trans people.
title: U.S. 'Welcome Corps' helps resettle LGBTQ refugees fleeing anti-gay crackdowns

description: Donald Trump says crime is rising. But several years of national data tell the opposite story: Crime is falling in cities and towns across the United States.
title: Trump says crime is out of control. The numbers tell a different story.

description: Two rapid-attribution studies released Tuesday found that human-caused global warming made Hurricane Helene stronger and wetter, elements that contributed to the storm's destructive power.
title: Helene rainfall boosted by human-driven climate change, studies find

description: The start of October is bringing little relief to parts of the western United States, where 36 million people are under heat alerts and sweltering temperatures are setting records into the fall.
title: Record heat makes for a sweltering start to October in the West

description: The Tennessee Bureau of Investigation said Wednesday it is looking into allegations against an Erwin plastics factory where several workers died after they were swept away by floodwaters from Hurricane Helene and some were still missing.
title: Tennessee investigating plastics factory after several workers trapped by Helene floodwaters died

description: Jacob Ingram describes clinging to a roll of plastic tubing after he and several of his coworkers at Tennessee's Impact Plastics were swept up in Helene's flooding. WBIR's Libby Cunningham reports.
title: 'I'll remember their faces forever': Flood victim describes struggle to survive

description: Vice President Kamala Harris’ campaign has been courting a group of Asian American voters, Filipino Americans, that may play a decisive role in the swing state of Nevada.
title: Why Harris is courting Filipino Americans in Nevada

description: Vice presidential hopefuls JD Vance and Tim Walz faced off in their first and only debate Tuesday night. Here's a fact check of what they got right and wrong.
title: Fact-checking the vice presidential debate between Vance and Walz

description: Trump is set to participate in two Texas fundraisers during his visit to the Lone Star state this week.
title: Trump to attend two fundraisers in Texas this week

description: Massive cleanup and recovery efforts are underway in the aftermath of Hurricane Helene. With roads washed out or blocked by debris, President Biden is set to take an aerial tour of the widespread destruction in the region. TODAY’s Craig Melvin reports from North Carolina.
title: Communities rally together after Hurricane Helene ravages region

description: President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris are set to take separate tours on Wednesday of the catastrophic damage resulting from Hurricane Helene, from which at least 150 people have died.
title: Biden heads to Carolinas and Harris to Georgia to view Hurricane Helene damage

description: With the new school year underway nationwide, law enforcement officials say they are seeing anti-semitic violence as the anniversary of the October 7th Hamas attacks on Israel approaches.
title: Five Jewish college students report being assaulted in the last month, as Oct. 7 anniversary approaches

description: NBC News is publishing the names of over 1,800 unclaimed individuals sent to the University of North Texas Health Science Center to help families find answers.
title: Naming the dead: Hundreds of unclaimed bodies were sent to a Texas medical school

description: David Jones was stuck at a bridge that had been washed away as he tried to drive to his daughter's wedding in Johnson City, Tennessee. So the marathon runner decided to walk the rest of the way. Frances Rivera has the full story on Early Today.
title: Dad walks miles to make daughter's wedding after Helene

description: Republican JD Vance dodged when asked to confirm Donald Trump lost in 2020 and whether he'll challenge the 2024 election results during the vice presidential debate.
title: 'Damning non-answer': Vance refuses to acknowledge Trump lost the 2020 election

description: Tim Walz conceded Tuesday night during the vice presidential debate that he “misspoke” in the past when he claimed that he was in Hong Kong during the crackdown in Tiananmen Square in which China’s military attacked and killed pro-democracy demonstrators.
title: Walz says he 'misspoke' when claiming to be in Hong Kong during Tiananmen Square crackdown

description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz said that Minnesota’s medical family leave program worked and added that if Vice President Kamala Harris is elected, she would prioritize establishing a federal paid family leave program.
title: Walz says that Harris is prioritizing a medical family leave program

description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz said his 17-year-old son witnessed a shooting at a community center while playing volleyball, when responding to a question about gun violence during the vice presidential debate.
title: Walz says his son witnessed a shooting while playing volleyball

description: The vice presidential candidates clashed on housing, with Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz saying he supported Harris’ plan for down payment assistance and new homes, while Ohio Sen. JD Vance backed Trump’s proposal to use federal lands and blamed undocumented immigrants for the housing shortage.
title: Walz and Vance clash over housing crisis

description: Sen. JD Vance claimed that the “gross majority” in the U.S. is committed with illegally obtained firearms, blaming the Biden-Harris administration’s border policy and increasing school security to curb gun violence in America.
title: Vance calls for more school security due to the ‘epidemic of gun violence’

description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz said he “misspoke” when claiming that he was in China during the Tiananmen Square protest in Hong Kong, stating, “It’s about understanding the world.”
title: Walz admits he ‘misspoke’ when saying he was in Hong Kong during Tiananmen Square protest

description: When asked about whether he supports abortion in the ninth month in Minnesota, Walz said "that's not what the bill says," adding that Trump "put this all into motion." Walz pivoted to examples of women and girls impacted by abortion access limitations or sexual violence, adding, "If you don't know an Amanda or a Hadley, you soon will."
title: Walz on abortion: Trump 'put this all into motion'

description: Ohio Sen. JD Vance stressed the importance of letting states handle abortion policy. Vance said he wants to support fertility treatments and make it more affordable to start a family.
title: Vance: ‘Let individual states make their abortion policy’

description: Ohio Sen. JD Vance addressed past criticisms he has made about former President Donald Trump saying he was "wrong" during the vice presidential debate.
title: Vance says he was ‘wrong’ about past Trump criticisms

description: Minnesota Gov. Walz and Ohio Sen. JD Vance clashed over the idea of "trusting the experts" in their administrations during the vice presidential debate.
title: Walz and Vance spar over trusting 'experts' during vice presidential debate

description: Ohio Sen. JD Vance expressed concern for "American citizens in Springfield whose lives have been devastated by Vice President Kamala Harris' open-border policies." He added that while he believes Walz wants to address the issue, he doesn't think Harris does.
title: Vance expresses concern for ‘American citizens’ living in Springfield

description: Ohio Sen. JD Vance discussed the position he and former President Trump would take on immigration and the border and claims Trump has made on the campaign trail.
title: Vance addresses how he would respond to 'historic immigration crisis'

description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz discussed the effects of Hurricane Helene and the response to climate change from the Biden-Harris administration during the  vice presidential debate.
title: Walz says Hurricane Helene is a 'horrific tragedy'

description: Ohio Sen. JD Vance responded to questions on reducing the impact of climate change and responds to the devastation from Hurricane Helene.
title: Vance appears to call climate change 'weird science'

description: Ohio Sen. JD Vance said “it is up to Israel” whether it would launch a pre-emptive strike on Iran. Vance said that former President Donald Trump delivered stability in the world by establishing “effective deterrence.”
title: Vance: ‘It is up to Israel’ whether it would launch pre-emptive strike on Iran

description: In the first question of the vice presidential debate, Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz discussed the response to Iran launching missiles towards Israel and said he and Vice President Harris would bring "steady leadership" to the White House.
title: Walz highlights importance of ‘steady leadership’ in response to Iran missile strike

description: While some families confirmed the deaths of their loved ones, others were still waiting for news of the missing, who were swept away by Hurricane Helene floodwaters.
title: Grief and anger mix as Tennessee plastic plant survivors say permission to leave came too late
